WEBVTT

00:04.131 --> 00:08.011
<b>I'm clockin' out early, hey, hey, hey.</b>

00:09.761 --> 00:12.011
<b>\h\h\hSpecial
Price</b>

00:09.761 --> 00:12.011
<b>Recommended</b>

00:09.761 --> 00:12.011
<b>Fresh Spring Vegetables</b>

00:09.761 --> 00:12.011
<b>Just In Today</b>

00:12.451 --> 00:15.011
<b>Next customer, please step this way.</b>

00:15.011 --> 00:17.141
<b>Oh... okay.</b>

00:29.451 --> 00:31.191
<b>That'll be 1,040 yen.</b>

00:31.191 --> 00:32.781
<b>Okay.</b>

00:33.161 --> 00:35.161
<b>Here's your change and receipt.</b>

00:35.771 --> 00:38.411
<b>You're close to getting 
your loyalty reward!</b>

00:38.711 --> 00:39.411
<b>Okay...</b>

00:39.681 --> 00:42.421
<b>We'll have a 50% discount coupon 
on mochi chips tomorrow.</b>

00:42.951 --> 00:44.371
<b>Thanks.</b>

00:52.831 --> 00:55.371
<b>I'll take over, Yamada-chan.</b>

00:55.371 --> 00:56.481
<b>Something's wrong.</b>

00:56.481 --> 00:57.431
<b>What?</b>

00:57.431 --> 01:01.691
<b>m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100</b>

00:57.431 --> 01:01.691
<b></b>What Usually Happens

00:57.431 --> 01:00.081
<b>Wow, I have so many points now.</b>

01:00.081 --> 01:01.691
<b>Thank you very much!</b>

01:02.171 --> 01:05.681
<b>My customer service 
didn't prove effective.</b>

01:05.681 --> 01:06.831
<b>On what?</b>

01:11.651 --> 01:14.571
<b><i>I want to smoke so bad.</i></b>

01:15.101 --> 01:17.361
<b>Come again, Sasaki-san.</b>

02:58.091 --> 03:00.171
<b>Tayama-san...</b>

03:03.181 --> 03:06.641
<b>I can't smoke here without her. 
It's not that easy.</b>

03:08.101 --> 03:10.191
<b>Heya, it's me, your easy girl.</b>

03:12.691 --> 03:13.881
<b>Tayama-san?!</b>

03:14.461 --> 03:16.151
<b>Wassup?</b>

03:16.691 --> 03:19.041
<b>Oh, did you just get off?</b>

03:19.041 --> 03:19.961
<b>Yep.</b>

03:19.961 --> 03:21.161
<b>Good work.</b>

03:21.741 --> 03:25.141
<b>Anyway, you want to smoke, right? 
Isn't that why you're here?</b>

03:25.141 --> 03:26.661
<b>Get in.</b>

03:25.761 --> 03:28.791
<b>O-Okay! Excuse me!</b>

03:37.121 --> 03:38.821
<b>That was one big sigh.</b>

03:39.441 --> 03:41.881
<b>Something got you down, Sasaki-san?</b>

03:41.881 --> 03:43.301
<b>Uh, well...</b>

03:43.721 --> 03:45.011
<b>I guess.</b>

03:49.321 --> 03:51.561
<b>Yamada-san was bothered by it.</b>

03:51.561 --> 03:55.651
<b>What? Did I act 
inappropriately back there?</b>

03:55.651 --> 03:56.821
<b>Not what I meant.</b>

03:57.411 --> 04:00.821
<b>She was worried about you 
because you were down in the dumps.</b>

04:03.941 --> 04:08.661
<b>She's such a considerate, 
thoughtful person.</b>

04:09.081 --> 04:11.091
<b>Thank you, too, Tayama-san.</b>

04:11.091 --> 04:13.281
<b>Hey, I'm just the messenger.</b>

04:13.281 --> 04:17.961
<b>What? But you came here 
just to tell me that, didn't you?</b>

04:19.211 --> 04:24.591
<b>Your hair's down, so I thought maybe 
you rushed here to talk to me.</b>

04:26.401 --> 04:30.691
<b>Hey, Tayama-san! You know you 
shouldn't blow smoke in someone's face!</b>

04:35.371 --> 04:38.501
<b>I couldn't be bothered 
doing my hair. That's all.</b>

04:39.381 --> 04:41.251
<b>And I passed on the message because...</b>

04:44.251 --> 04:46.101
<b>I'm not telling you.</b>

04:46.591 --> 04:49.691
<b>You can blame yourself 
for getting cheeky tonight.</b>

04:52.291 --> 04:54.101
<b>Cheeky? What?</b>

04:54.621 --> 04:56.601
<b>H-How do you mean?</b>

04:56.601 --> 04:58.561
<b>Too cheeky for such a dense guy.</b>

04:58.561 --> 05:00.881
<b>Excuse me? I am not dense.</b>

05:06.131 --> 05:08.461
<b>Am I really that dense?</b>

05:08.461 --> 05:09.641
<b>What's the matter?</b>

05:10.251 --> 05:12.491
<b>Tayama-san, uh...</b>

05:13.371 --> 05:17.481
<b>Could I get your unbiased thoughts 
on something? I'd appreciate it.</b>

05:17.481 --> 05:18.621
<b>What is it?</b>

05:20.221 --> 05:21.821
<b>Am I a scary guy?</b>

05:23.931 --> 05:25.641
<b>Are you okay?</b>

05:25.641 --> 05:28.291
<b>Where'd that hilarious question come from?</b>

05:28.291 --> 05:29.341
<b>"Hilarious"?</b>

05:30.121 --> 05:31.331
<b>Well, you see...</b>

05:35.131 --> 05:39.671
<b>I made a fresh-out-of-college 
hire cry today.</b>

05:39.671 --> 05:44.731
<b>What, Sasaki-san, are you the yelly 
type at work? That's so funny.</b>

05:44.731 --> 05:47.141
<b><i>Hey! Now look here, you... You...!</i></b>

05:47.141 --> 05:49.051
<b>No! Absolutely not!</b>

05:49.991 --> 05:52.181
<b>She made a really trivial mistake,</b>

05:52.181 --> 05:54.901
<b>so I tried to cheer her up,</b>

05:54.901 --> 05:57.631
<b>but I think she took 
what I said the opposite way.</b>

06:03.511 --> 06:05.371
<b>Just do better next time, okay?</b>

06:07.951 --> 06:09.451
<b>Huh? I, uh...</b>

06:11.451 --> 06:13.801
<b>What is wrong with you, Sasaki-kun?!</b>

06:13.801 --> 06:15.451
<b>I'm terribly sorry, sir.</b>

06:15.451 --> 06:18.701
<b>Sasaki-san got torn a new one.</b>

06:18.701 --> 06:20.441
<b>I heard he made a new hire cry.</b>

06:20.441 --> 06:22.711
<b>What? Sasaki-san, of all people?!</b>

06:25.681 --> 06:29.761
<b>I'd feel so bad if she came 
to hate her job because of me.</b>

06:36.511 --> 06:38.481
<b>I don't see the problem.</b>

06:38.481 --> 06:43.671
<b>Your workplace is basically a sweatshop, 
making you work so late all the time.</b>

06:43.671 --> 06:45.121
<b>She'll probably quit either way.</b>

06:45.121 --> 06:47.651
<b>Don't say that, Tayama-san...</b>

06:49.751 --> 06:53.991
<b>Besides, if she's a fresh graduate, 
she only just joined the company, right?</b>

06:54.831 --> 06:59.851
<b>She'll eventually find out 
that you're a good person.</b>

07:03.561 --> 07:06.701
<b>Well, if she sticks around that long.</b>

07:07.291 --> 07:08.861
<b>Thanks for saying so.</b>

07:13.321 --> 07:17.351
<b>I'm sure Yamada-san would never 
find herself in this situation.</b>

07:17.771 --> 07:19.441
<b>Why bring her up there?</b>

07:19.441 --> 07:26.281
<b>I just thought, she'd never scare 
new hires to the point of tears.</b>

07:27.711 --> 07:32.781
<b>Unlike me and my intimidating 
appearance, you mean?</b>

07:32.781 --> 07:34.921
<b>That's not what I meant.</b>

07:34.921 --> 07:40.851
<b>True, she's more likely 
to be disrespected than feared.</b>

07:40.851 --> 07:43.001
<b>Disrespected?</b>

07:45.211 --> 07:47.701
<b>I really think she's incredible.</b>

07:47.701 --> 07:50.271
<b>She's bright and cheery, 
even when working at odd hours,</b>

07:50.271 --> 07:53.101
<b>and she even looks out 
for troublesome customers like me.</b>

07:53.551 --> 07:57.191
<b>I wish I could go about things 
with a smile like her.</b>

08:02.291 --> 08:06.521
<b>Supermarkets train their employees hard 
to have the perfect smile.</b>

08:06.521 --> 08:10.121
<b>Oh, really? Does that mean you, too?</b>

08:10.121 --> 08:10.871
<b>Yep.</b>

08:11.191 --> 08:13.281
<b>Your eyes have to be 
upturned and crescent.</b>

08:13.281 --> 08:14.951
<b>Lift your facial muscles,</b>

08:15.371 --> 08:17.421
<b>and show your upper teeth.</b>

08:19.201 --> 08:20.241
<b>Like so!</b>

08:23.251 --> 08:26.591
<b>T-Tamaya-san, you...</b>

08:29.501 --> 08:30.301
<b>Huh?</b>

08:32.771 --> 08:33.551
<b>Wha?</b>

08:34.211 --> 08:36.351
<b>Sorry. I'm really sorry.</b>

08:37.061 --> 08:40.101
<b>It's just, that really took me aback.</b>

08:40.781 --> 08:44.181
<b>You look great when you're acting 
all cutesy, too, Tayama-san.</b>

08:47.611 --> 08:48.511
<b>Huh?</b>

08:49.111 --> 08:50.911
<b>T... Tayama-san?</b>

08:52.881 --> 08:55.601
<b>No, I should be apologizing to you.</b>

08:55.601 --> 08:58.621
<b>Rather than just demonstrating, 
I should have instructed you directly.</b>

08:58.621 --> 09:00.871
<b>S-Sowwy, 'ayama-han!</b>

09:00.871 --> 09:01.871
<b>A you ma'?</b>

09:01.871 --> 09:04.681
<b>I din't mean anying 'y it!</b>

09:07.381 --> 09:10.411
<b>Okay. That'll do for smile practice.</b>

09:17.411 --> 09:19.281
<b>I'm sorry, okay?</b>

09:20.711 --> 09:23.391
<b>Remember that feeling and practice more.</b>

09:23.391 --> 09:24.201
<b>I...</b>

09:24.201 --> 09:24.941
<b>Got that?</b>

09:24.941 --> 09:25.751
<b>Yes, ma'am!</b>

09:26.731 --> 09:30.021
<b>Genki Trading</b>

09:29.101 --> 09:33.031
<b>I'm really sorry 
for breaking down yesterday!</b>

09:34.421 --> 09:37.781
<b>I didn't mean to cry, but...</b>

09:38.241 --> 09:40.801
<b>I was just so overwhelmed.</b>

09:40.801 --> 09:42.821
<b>Let's talk outside. 
It's too smoky in here.</b>

09:42.821 --> 09:44.261
<b>No, that's fine.</b>

09:44.791 --> 09:48.881
<b>I'm truly sorry for making you out 
to be the bad guy.</b>

09:48.881 --> 09:51.881
<b>Don't be. I should've thought 
about my phrasing, too.</b>

09:51.881 --> 09:54.301
<b>There's no need! I...</b>

09:54.301 --> 09:57.901
<b>I knew you were a good person. 
I shouldn't have misunderstood.</b>

09:59.621 --> 10:04.981
<b>She'll eventually find out 
that you're a good person.</b>

10:08.641 --> 10:11.641
<b>It's totally normal to mess up at first. 
In fact, you're expected to.</b>

10:11.641 --> 10:13.491
<b>Don't let it get to you.</b>

10:13.491 --> 10:16.351
<b>And if you ever have any questions, 
don't hesitate to ask.</b>

10:16.791 --> 10:18.261
<b>Thank you very much.</b>

10:21.251 --> 10:22.511
<b>What a smooth operator.</b>

10:22.511 --> 10:25.201
<b>Don't ruin it!</b>

10:30.031 --> 10:32.961
<b>Next customer, please step this way.</b>

10:37.111 --> 10:39.471
<b>Here's your receipt.</b>

10:40.381 --> 10:41.971
<b>Thank you.</b>

10:42.371 --> 10:44.061
<b>Thank you! Come again!</b>

10:55.631 --> 10:58.361
<b><i>You look great when you're 
acting all cutesy too,</i></b>

10:58.931 --> 11:00.141
<b><i>Tayama-san.</i></b>

11:01.191 --> 11:03.181
<b>Don't laugh at that, Sasaki.</b>

11:06.241 --> 11:08.141
<b><i>You see it all the time.</i></b>

11:09.081 --> 11:12.711
<b>Translation: Sriram Gurunathan</b>

11:13.211 --> 11:16.841
<b>Editing & Typesetting: Geoff Mazzolini
Subtitle Timing: Krzysztof Kunc</b>

11:17.551 --> 11:20.801
<b>Quality Check: Zachary Carlysle
Translation Check: Sho Stifler</b>
